189 template <class T>
190 class Local {
191  public:
192  V8_INLINE Local() : val_(nullptr) {}
193  template <class S>
194  V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
195  : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
201  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
202  }
203 
207  V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
208 
212  V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = nullptr; }
213 
214  V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
215 
216  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
217 
228  template <class S>
229  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
230  internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
231  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
232  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
233  if (b == nullptr) return false;
234  return *a == *b;
235  }
236 
237  template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
238  const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
239  internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
240  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
241  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
242  if (b == nullptr) return false;
243  return *a == *b;
244  }
245 
256  template <class S>
257  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
258  return !operator==(that);
259  }
260 
261  template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
262  const Persistent<S>& that) const {
263  return !operator==(that);
264  }
265 
271  template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
272 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
273  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
274  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
275  if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
276 #endif
277  return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
278  }
279 
285  template <class S>
286  V8_INLINE Local<S> As() const {
287  return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
288  }
289 
295  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
296  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
297  const PersistentBase<T>& that);
298  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
299  const TracedReferenceBase<T>& that);
300 
301  private:
302  friend class Utils;
303  template<class F> friend class Eternal;
304  template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
305  template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
306  template<class F> friend class Local;
307  template <class F>
308  friend class MaybeLocal;
309  template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
310  template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
311  friend class String;
312  friend class Object;
313  friend class Context;
314  friend class Isolate;
315  friend class Private;
316  template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
317  friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
318  friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
319  friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
320  friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
321  friend class HandleScope;
322  friend class EscapableHandleScope;
323  template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
324  friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
325  template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
326  template <class F>
327  friend class ReturnValue;
328  template <class F>
329  friend class Traced;
330  template <class F>
331  friend class TracedGlobal;
332  template <class F>
333  friend class TracedReferenceBase;
334  template <class F>
335  friend class TracedReference;
336 
337  explicit V8_INLINE Local(T* that) : val_(that) {}
338  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
339  T* val_;
340 };

360 template <class T>
361 class MaybeLocal {
362  public:
363  V8_INLINE MaybeLocal() : val_(nullptr) {}
364  template <class S>
365  V8_INLINE MaybeLocal(Local<S> that)
366  : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
367  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
368  }
369 
370  V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
371 
376  template <class S>
377  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
378  out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
379  return !IsEmpty();
380  }
381 
386  V8_INLINE Local<T> ToLocalChecked();
387 
392  template <class S>
393  V8_INLINE Local<S> FromMaybe(Local<S> default_value) const {
394  return IsEmpty() ? default_value : Local<S>(val_);
395  }
396 
397  private:
398  T* val_;
399 };

405 template <class T> class Eternal {
406  public:
407  V8_INLINE Eternal() : val_(nullptr) {}
408  template <class S>
409  V8_INLINE Eternal(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle) : val_(nullptr) {
410  Set(isolate, handle);
411  }
412  // Can only be safely called if already set.
413  V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate) const;
414  V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
415  template<class S> V8_INLINE void Set(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle);
416 
417  private:
418  T* val_;
419 };

422 static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
423 static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
424 
425 template <typename T>
426 class WeakCallbackInfo {
427  public:
428  typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
429 
430  WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
431  void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
432  Callback* callback)
433  : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
434  for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
435  embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
436  }
437  }
438 
439  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
440  V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
441  V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
442 
443  // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
444  // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
445  // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
446  // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
447  // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
448  // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
449  void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
450 
451  private:
452  Isolate* isolate_;
453  T* parameter_;
454  Callback* callback_;
455  void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
456 };
457 
458 
459 // kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
460 // will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
461 // will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
462 // actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
463 // possible to request a second pass callback.
464 enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };
465 
479 template <class T> class PersistentBase {
480  public:
485  V8_INLINE void Reset();
490  template <class S>
491  V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other);
492 
497  template <class S>
498  V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& other);
499 
500  V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
501  V8_INLINE void Empty() { val_ = 0; }
502 
503  V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate) const {
504  return Local<T>::New(isolate, *this);
505  }
506 
507  template <class S>
508  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
509  internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
510  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
511  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
512  if (b == nullptr) return false;
513  return *a == *b;
514  }
515 
516  template <class S>
517  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
518  internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
519  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
520  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
521  if (b == nullptr) return false;
522  return *a == *b;
523  }
524 
525  template <class S>
526  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
527  return !operator==(that);
528  }
529 
530  template <class S>
531  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
532  return !operator==(that);
533  }
534 
547  template <typename P>
548  V8_INLINE void SetWeak(P* parameter,
549  typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
550  WeakCallbackType type);
551 
559  V8_INLINE void SetWeak();
560 
561  template<typename P>
562  V8_INLINE P* ClearWeak();
563 
564  // TODO(dcarney): remove this.
565  V8_INLINE void ClearWeak() { ClearWeak<void>(); }
566 
573  V8_INLINE void AnnotateStrongRetainer(const char* label);
574 
576  V8_INLINE bool IsWeak() const;
577 
581  V8_INLINE void SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id);
582 
587  V8_INLINE uint16_t WrapperClassId() const;
588 
589  PersistentBase(const PersistentBase& other) = delete; // NOLINT
590  void operator=(const PersistentBase&) = delete;
591 
592  private:
593  friend class Isolate;
594  friend class Utils;
595  template<class F> friend class Local;
596  template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
597  template <class F>
598  friend class Global;
599  template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
600  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
601  template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
602  friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
603  template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
604  friend class Object;
605 
606  explicit V8_INLINE PersistentBase(T* val) : val_(val) {}
607  V8_INLINE static T* New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
608 
609  T* val_;
610 };

619 template<class T>
620 class NonCopyablePersistentTraits {
621  public:
622  typedef Persistent<T, NonCopyablePersistentTraits<T> > NonCopyablePersistent;
623  static const bool kResetInDestructor = false;
624  template<class S, class M>
625  V8_INLINE static void Copy(const Persistent<S, M>& source,
626  NonCopyablePersistent* dest) {
627  static_assert(sizeof(S) < 0,
628  "NonCopyablePersistentTraits::Copy is not instantiable");
629  }
630 };

637 template<class T>
638 struct CopyablePersistentTraits {
639  typedef Persistent<T, CopyablePersistentTraits<T> > CopyablePersistent;
640  static const bool kResetInDestructor = true;
641  template<class S, class M>
642  static V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M>& source,
643  CopyablePersistent* dest) {
644  // do nothing, just allow copy
645  }
646 };

657 template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
658  public:
662  V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
668  template <class S>
669  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
670  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
671  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
672  }
678  template <class S, class M2>
679  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
680  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
681  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
682  }
689  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {
690  Copy(that);
691  }
692  template <class S, class M2>
693  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
694  Copy(that);
695  }
696  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) {
697  Copy(that);
698  return *this;
699  }
700  template <class S, class M2>
701  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
702  Copy(that);
703  return *this;
704  }
710  V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
711  if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
712  }
713 
714  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
715  template <class S>
716  V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
717 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
718  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
719  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
720  if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
721 #endif
722  return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
723  }
724 
725  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
726  template <class S>
727  V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
728  return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
729  }
730 
731  private:
732  friend class Isolate;
733  friend class Utils;
734  template<class F> friend class Local;
735  template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
736  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
737 
738  explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
739  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
740  template<class S, class M2>
741  V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
742 };

838 template <typename T>
839 class TracedReferenceBase {
840  public:
845  bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
846 
851  V8_INLINE void Reset();
852 
856  Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate) const { return Local<T>::New(isolate, *this); }
857 
858  template <class S>
859  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const TracedReferenceBase<S>& that) const {
860  internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(val_);
861  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
862  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
863  if (b == nullptr) return false;
864  return *a == *b;
865  }
866 
867  template <class S>
868  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
869  internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(val_);
870  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
871  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
872  if (b == nullptr) return false;
873  return *a == *b;
874  }
875 
876  template <class S>
877  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const TracedReferenceBase<S>& that) const {
878  return !operator==(that);
879  }
880 
881  template <class S>
882  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
883  return !operator==(that);
884  }
885 
889  V8_INLINE void SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id);
890 
895  V8_INLINE uint16_t WrapperClassId() const;
896 
897  template <class S>
898  V8_INLINE TracedReferenceBase<S>& As() const {
899  return reinterpret_cast<TracedReferenceBase<S>&>(
900  const_cast<TracedReferenceBase<T>&>(*this));
901  }
902 
903  private:
904  enum DestructionMode { kWithDestructor, kWithoutDestructor };
905 
909  TracedReferenceBase() = default;
910 
911  V8_INLINE static T* New(Isolate* isolate, T* that, void* slot,
912  DestructionMode destruction_mode);
913 
914  T* val_ = nullptr;
915 
916  friend class EmbedderHeapTracer;
917  template <typename F>
918  friend class Local;
919  friend class Object;
920  template <typename F>
921  friend class TracedGlobal;
922  template <typename F>
923  friend class TracedReference;
924  template <typename F>
925  friend class ReturnValue;
926 };

932 template <typename T>
933 class TracedGlobal : public TracedReferenceBase<T> {
934  public:
935  using TracedReferenceBase<T>::Reset;
936 
940  ~TracedGlobal() { this->Reset(); }
941 
945  TracedGlobal() : TracedReferenceBase<T>() {}
946 
953  template <class S>
954  TracedGlobal(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that) : TracedReferenceBase<T>() {
955  this->val_ = this->New(isolate, that.val_, &this->val_,
956  TracedReferenceBase<T>::kWithDestructor);
957  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
958  }
959 
963  V8_INLINE TracedGlobal(TracedGlobal&& other) {
964  // Forward to operator=.
965  *this = std::move(other);
966  }
967 
971  template <typename S>
972  V8_INLINE TracedGlobal(TracedGlobal<S>&& other) {
973  // Forward to operator=.
974  *this = std::move(other);
975  }
976 
980  V8_INLINE TracedGlobal(const TracedGlobal& other) {
981  // Forward to operator=;
982  *this = other;
983  }
984 
988  template <typename S>
989  V8_INLINE TracedGlobal(const TracedGlobal<S>& other) {
990  // Forward to operator=;
991  *this = other;
992  }
993 
997  V8_INLINE TracedGlobal& operator=(TracedGlobal&& rhs);
998 
1002  template <class S>
1003  V8_INLINE TracedGlobal& operator=(TracedGlobal<S>&& rhs);
1004 
1011  V8_INLINE TracedGlobal& operator=(const TracedGlobal& rhs);
1012 
1019  template <class S>
1020  V8_INLINE TracedGlobal& operator=(const TracedGlobal<S>& rhs);
1021 
1026  template <class S>
1027  V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other);
1028 
1029  template <class S>
1030  V8_INLINE TracedGlobal<S>& As() const {
1031  return reinterpret_cast<TracedGlobal<S>&>(
1032  const_cast<TracedGlobal<T>&>(*this));
1033  }
1034 
1045  V8_INLINE void SetFinalizationCallback(
1046  void* parameter, WeakCallbackInfo<void>::Callback callback);
1047 };

1060 template <typename T>
1061 class TracedReference : public TracedReferenceBase<T> {
1062  public:
1063  using TracedReferenceBase<T>::Reset;
1064 
1068  TracedReference() : TracedReferenceBase<T>() {}
1069 
1076  template <class S>
1077  TracedReference(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that) : TracedReferenceBase<T>() {
1078  this->val_ = this->New(isolate, that.val_, &this->val_,
1079  TracedReferenceBase<T>::kWithoutDestructor);
1080  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
1081  }
1082 
1087  V8_INLINE TracedReference(TracedReference&& other) {
1088  // Forward to operator=.
1089  *this = std::move(other);
1090  }
1091 
1096  template <typename S>
1097  V8_INLINE TracedReference(TracedReference<S>&& other) {
1098  // Forward to operator=.
1099  *this = std::move(other);
1100  }
1101 
1106  V8_INLINE TracedReference(const TracedReference& other) {
1107  // Forward to operator=;
1108  *this = other;
1109  }
1110 
1115  template <typename S>
1116  V8_INLINE TracedReference(const TracedReference<S>& other) {
1117  // Forward to operator=;
1118  *this = other;
1119  }
1120 
1124  V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(TracedReference&& rhs);
1125 
1129  template <class S>
1130  V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(TracedReference<S>&& rhs);
1131 
1135  V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(const TracedReference& rhs);
1136 
1140  template <class S>
1141  V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(const TracedReference<S>& rhs);
1142 
1147  template <class S>
1148  V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other);
1149 
1150  template <class S>
1151  V8_INLINE TracedReference<S>& As() const {
1152  return reinterpret_cast<TracedReference<S>&>(
1153  const_cast<TracedReference<T>&>(*this));
1154  }
1155 };

1336 class ScriptOriginOptions {
1337  public:
1338  V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
1339  bool is_opaque = false, bool is_wasm = false,
1340  bool is_module = false)
1341  : flags_((is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
1342  (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0) |
1343  (is_module ? kIsModule : 0)) {}
1344  V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
1345  : flags_(flags &
1346  (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm | kIsModule)) {}
1347 
1348  bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
1349  return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
1350  }
1351  bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
1352  bool IsWasm() const { return (flags_ & kIsWasm) != 0; }
1353  bool IsModule() const { return (flags_ & kIsModule) != 0; }
1354 
1355  int Flags() const { return flags_; }
1356 
1357  private:
1358  enum {
1359  kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1,
1360  kIsOpaque = 1 << 1,
1361  kIsWasm = 1 << 2,
1362  kIsModule = 1 << 3
1363  };
1364  const int flags_;
1365 };

1635 class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1636  public:
1644  struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1645  enum BufferPolicy {
1646  BufferNotOwned,
1647  BufferOwned
1648  };
1649 
1650  CachedData()
1651  : data(nullptr),
1652  length(0),
1653  rejected(false),
1654  buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1655 
1656  // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1657  // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1658  // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1659  // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1660  CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1661  BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1662  ~CachedData();
1663  // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1664  // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1665  const uint8_t* data;
1666  int length;
1667  bool rejected;
1668  BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1669 
1670  // Prevent copying.
1671  CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1672  CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1673  };

1689  // alive.
1690  V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;

1693

3714 
3715  // Implements Object.DefineProperty(O, P, Attributes), see Ecma-262 19.1.2.4.
3716  //
3717  // The defineProperty function is used to add an own property or
3718  // update the attributes of an existing own property of an object.
3719  //
3720  // Both data and accessor descriptors can be used.
3721  //
3722  // In general, CreateDataProperty is faster, however, does not allow
3723  // for specifying attributes or an accessor descriptor.
3724  //
3725  // The PropertyDescriptor can change when redefining a property.
3726  //
3727  // Returns true on success.
3728  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> DefineProperty(
3729  Local<Context> context, Local<Name> key,
3730  PropertyDescriptor& descriptor); // NOLINT(runtime/references)

4226 template<typename T>
4227 class ReturnValue {
4228  public:
4229  template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
4230  : value_(that.value_) {
4231  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
4232  }
4233  // Local setters
4234  template <typename S>
4235  V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
4236  template <typename S>
4237  V8_INLINE void Set(const TracedReferenceBase<S>& handle);
4238  template <typename S>
4239  V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
4240  // Fast primitive setters
4241  V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
4242  V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
4243  V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
4244  V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
4245  // Fast JS primitive setters
4246  V8_INLINE void SetNull();
4247  V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
4248  V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
4249  // Convenience getter for Isolate
4250  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const;
4251 
4252  // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
4253  template <typename S>
4254  V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
4255 
4256  // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
4257  // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
4258  // value.
4259  V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
4260 
4261  private:
4262  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
4263  template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
4264  template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
4265  template <class F, class G, class H>
4266  friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
4267  V8_INLINE void SetInternal(internal::Address value) { *value_ = value; }
4268  V8_INLINE internal::Address GetDefaultValue();
4269  V8_INLINE explicit ReturnValue(internal::Address* slot);
4270  internal::Address* value_;
4271 };

6962 class V8_EXPORT Extension { // NOLINT

6967  const char** deps = nullptr, int source_length = -1);
6968  virtual ~Extension() { delete source_; }

6970  Isolate* isolate, Local<String> name) {
6971  return Local<FunctionTemplate>();
6972  }
6973 
6974  const char* name() const { return name_; }
6975  size_t source_length() const { return source_length_; }
6976  const String::ExternalOneByteStringResource* source() const {
6977  return source_;
6978  }
6979  int dependency_count() const { return dep_count_; }
6980  const char** dependencies() const { return deps_; }
6981  void set_auto_enable(bool value) { auto_enable_ = value; }
6982  bool auto_enable() { return auto_enable_; }
6983 
6984  // Disallow copying and assigning.
6985  Extension(const Extension&) = delete;
6986  void operator=(const Extension&) = delete;
6987 
6988  private:
6989  const char* name_;
6990  size_t source_length_; // expected to initialize before source_
6991  String::ExternalOneByteStringResource* source_;
6992  int dep_count_;
6993  const char** deps_;
6994  bool auto_enable_;
6995 };

7690 
7696 struct JitCodeEvent {
7697  enum EventType {
7698  CODE_ADDED,
7699  CODE_MOVED,
7700  CODE_REMOVED,
7701  CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
7702  CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
7703  CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
7704  };
7705  // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
7706  // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
7707  // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
7708  // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
7709  // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
7710  enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
7711 
7712  // There are two different kinds of JitCodeEvents, one for JIT code generated
7713  // by the optimizing compiler, and one for byte code generated for the
7714  // interpreter. For JIT_CODE events, the |code_start| member of the event
7715  // points to the beginning of jitted assembly code, while for BYTE_CODE
7716  // events, |code_start| points to the first bytecode of the interpreted
7717  // function.
7718  enum CodeType { BYTE_CODE, JIT_CODE };
7719 
7720  // Type of event.
7721  EventType type;
7722  CodeType code_type;
7723  // Start of the instructions.
7724  void* code_start;
7725  // Size of the instructions.
7726  size_t code_len;
7727  // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
7728  Local<UnboundScript> script;
7729  // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
7730  // code line information which is returned from the
7731  // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
7732  // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
7733  void* user_data;
7734 
7735  struct name_t {
7736  // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
7737  // zero-terminated.
7738  const char* str;
7739  // Number of chars in str.
7740  size_t len;
7741  };
7742 
7743  struct line_info_t {
7744  // PC offset
7745  size_t offset;
7746  // Code position
7747  size_t pos;
7748  // The position type.
7749  PositionType position_type;
7750  };
7751 
7752  struct wasm_source_info_t {
7753  // Source file name.
7754  const char* filename;
7755  // Length of filename.
7756  size_t filename_size;
7757  // Line number table, which maps offsets of JITted code to line numbers of
7758  // source file.
7759  const line_info_t* line_number_table;
7760  // Number of entries in the line number table.
7761  size_t line_number_table_size;
7762  };
7763 
7764  wasm_source_info_t* wasm_source_info;
7765 
7766  union {
7767  // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
7768  struct name_t name;
7769 
7770  // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
7771  struct line_info_t line_info;
7772 
7773  // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
7774  void* new_code_start;
7775  };
7776 
7777  Isolate* isolate;
7778 };
7779 
7785 enum RAILMode : unsigned {
7786  // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
7787  // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
7788  // Throughput may be throttled.
7789  PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
7790  // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
7791  // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
7792  // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
7793  PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
7794  // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
7795  // in this mode.
7796  PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
7797  // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
7798  // turn off latency optimizations.
7799  PERFORMANCE_LOAD
7800 };
7801

9915 
9926 template <class T>
9927 class Maybe {
9928  public:
9929  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
9930  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
9931 
9935  V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
9936 
9941  V8_INLINE void Check() const {
9942  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
9943  }
9944 
9949  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
9950  if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
9951  return IsJust();
9952  }
9953 
9958  V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
9959  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
9960  return value_;
9961  }
9962 
9967  V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
9968  return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
9969  }
9970 
9971  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
9972  return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
9973  (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
9974  }
9975 
9976  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
9977  return !operator==(other);
9978  }
9979 
9980  private:
9981  Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
9982  explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
9983 
9984  bool has_value_;
9985  T value_;
9986 
9987  template <class U>
9988  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
9989  template <class U>
9990  friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
9991 };

9993 template <class T>
9994 inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
9995  return Maybe<T>();
9996 }
9997 
9998 template <class T>
9999 inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
10000  return Maybe<T>(t);
10001 }
10002 
10003 // A template specialization of Maybe<T> for the case of T = void.
10004 template <>
10005 class Maybe<void> {
10006  public:
10007  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !is_valid_; }
10008  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return is_valid_; }
10009 
10010  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
10011  return IsJust() == other.IsJust();
10012  }
10013 
10014  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
10015  return !operator==(other);
10016  }
10017 
10018  private:
10019  struct JustTag {};
10020 
10021  Maybe() : is_valid_(false) {}
10022  explicit Maybe(JustTag) : is_valid_(true) {}
10023 
10024  bool is_valid_;
10025 
10026  template <class U>
10027  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
10028  friend Maybe<void> JustVoid();
10029 };
10030 
10031 inline Maybe<void> JustVoid() { return Maybe<void>(Maybe<void>::JustTag()); }

10723 template <class T>
10724 Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that) {
10725  if (that == nullptr) return Local<T>();
10726  T* that_ptr = that;
10727  internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that_ptr);
10728  return Local<T>(reinterpret_cast<T*>(HandleScope::CreateHandle(
10729  reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate), *p)));
10730 }

10738  V8::Eternalize(isolate, reinterpret_cast<Value*>(*handle)));
10739 }

10769  if (that == nullptr) return nullptr;

10771  return reinterpret_cast<T*>(
10772  V8::GlobalizeReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate),
10773  p));
10774 }

10777 template <class T, class M>
10778 template <class S, class M2>
10779 void Persistent<T, M>::Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) {
10780  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
10781  this->Reset();
10782  if (that.IsEmpty()) return;
10783  internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
10784  this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyGlobalReference(p));
10785  M::Copy(that, this);
10786 }

10792  return I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_)) ==
10793  I::kNodeStateIsWeakValue;
10794 }

10830  WeakCallbackType type) {
10831  typedef typename WeakCallbackInfo<void>::Callback Callback;
10832 #if (__GNUC__ >= 8) && !defined(__clang__)
10833 #pragma GCC diagnostic push
10834 #pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wcast-function-type"
10835 #endif
10836  V8::MakeWeak(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_), parameter,
10837  reinterpret_cast<Callback>(callback), type);
10838 #if (__GNUC__ >= 8) && !defined(__clang__)
10839 #pragma GCC diagnostic pop
10840 #endif
10841 }

10880 template <class T>
10881 Global<T>::Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) {
10882  if (other.val_ != nullptr) {
10883  V8::MoveGlobalReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&other.val_),
10884  reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
10885  other.val_ = nullptr;
10886  }
10887 }
10888 
10889 template <class T>
10890 template <class S>
10891 Global<T>& Global<T>::operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) {
10892  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
10893  if (this != &rhs) {
10894  this->Reset();
10895  if (rhs.val_ != nullptr) {
10896  this->val_ = rhs.val_;
10897  V8::MoveGlobalReference(
10898  reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&rhs.val_),
10899  reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
10900  rhs.val_ = nullptr;
10901  }
10902  }
10903  return *this;
10904 }

10912  reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate), p,

10914  destruction_mode == kWithDestructor));

11074 template <typename S>
11075 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(const Local<S> handle) {
11076  static_assert(std::is_void<T>::value || std::is_base_of<T, S>::value,
11077  "type check");
11078  if (V8_UNLIKELY(handle.IsEmpty())) {
11079  *value_ = GetDefaultValue();
11080  } else {
11081  *value_ = *reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(*handle);
11082  }
11083 }
11084 
11085 template<typename T>
11086 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(double i) {
11087  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Number>::value, "type check");
11088  Set(Number::New(GetIsolate(), i));
11089 }
11090 
11091 template<typename T>
11092 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
11093  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Integer>::value, "type check");
11094  typedef internal::Internals I;
11095  if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
11096  *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
11097  return;
11098  }
11099  Set(Integer::New(GetIsolate(), i));
11100 }
11101 
11102 template<typename T>
11103 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
11104  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Integer>::value, "type check");
11105  // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
11106  bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
11107  if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
11108  Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
11109  return;
11110  }
11111  Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
11112 }
11113 
11114 template<typename T>
11115 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
11116  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Boolean>::value, "type check");
11117  typedef internal::Internals I;
11118  int root_index;
11119  if (value) {
11120  root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
11121  } else {
11122  root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
11123  }
11124  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
11125 }
11126 
11127 template<typename T>
11128 void ReturnValue<T>::SetNull() {
11129  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Primitive>::value, "type check");
11130  typedef internal::Internals I;
11131  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kNullValueRootIndex);
11132 }

11137  typedef internal::Internals I;

11139 }

11148 template <typename T>
11149 Isolate* ReturnValue<T>::GetIsolate() const {
11150  // Isolate is always the pointer below the default value on the stack.
11151  return *reinterpret_cast<Isolate**>(&value_[-2]);
11152 }
11153 
11154 template <typename T>
11155 Local<Value> ReturnValue<T>::Get() const {
11156  typedef internal::Internals I;
11157  if (*value_ == *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kTheHoleValueRootIndex))
11158  return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
11159  return Local<Value>::New(GetIsolate(), reinterpret_cast<Value*>(value_));
11160 }

11166 }

11168 template <typename T>
11169 internal::Address ReturnValue<T>::GetDefaultValue() {
11170  // Default value is always the pointer below value_ on the stack.
11171  return value_[-1];
11172 }

11180 template<typename T>
11181 Local<Value> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::operator[](int i) const {
11182  // values_ points to the first argument (not the receiver).
11183  if (i < 0 || length_ <= i) return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
11184 #ifdef V8_REVERSE_JSARGS
11185  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(values_ + i));
11186 #else
11187  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(values_ - i));
11188 #endif
11189 }

11195 #ifdef V8_REVERSE_JSARGS
11196  return Local<Object>(reinterpret_cast<Object*>(values_ - 1));
11197 #else
11198  return Local<Object>(reinterpret_cast<Object*>(values_ + 1));
11199 #endif
11200 }

11353 
11354 Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
11355 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11356  typedef internal::Address A;
11357  typedef internal::Internals I;
11358  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11359  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11360  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11361  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11362  if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11363  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11364  instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType) {
11365  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11366  A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(obj, offset);
11367 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
11368  // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
11369  // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
11370  value = I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(obj, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
11371 #endif
11372  internal::Isolate* isolate =
11373  internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(obj);
11374  A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
11375  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
11376  }
11377 #endif
11378  return SlowGetInternalField(index);
11379 }
11380 
11381 
11382 void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
11383 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11384  typedef internal::Address A;
11385  typedef internal::Internals I;
11386  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11387  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11388  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11389  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11390  if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11391  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11392  instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType)) {
11393  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11394  internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(obj);
11395  A value = I::ReadExternalPointerField(isolate, obj, offset);
11396  return reinterpret_cast<void*>(value);
11397  }
11398 #endif
11399  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
11400 }

11410 Local<String> String::Empty(Isolate* isolate) {

11415  return Local<String>(reinterpret_cast<String*>(slot));
11416 }

11418 
11419 String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
11420  typedef internal::Address A;
11421  typedef internal::Internals I;
11422  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11423 
11424  ExternalStringResource* result;
11425  if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
11426  internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(obj);
11427  A value =
11428  I::ReadExternalPointerField(isolate, obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
11429  result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
11430  } else {
11431  result = GetExternalStringResourceSlow();
11432  }
11433 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11434  VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
11435 #endif
11436  return result;
11437 }
11438 
11439 
11440 String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
11441  String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
11442  typedef internal::Address A;
11443  typedef internal::Internals I;
11444  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11445  int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
11446  *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
11447  ExternalStringResourceBase* resource;
11448  if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
11449  type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
11450  internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(obj);
11451  A value =
11452  I::ReadExternalPointerField(isolate, obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
11453  resource = reinterpret_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
11454  } else {
11455  resource = GetExternalStringResourceBaseSlow(encoding_out);
11456  }
11457 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11458  VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
11459 #endif
11460  return resource;
11461 }

11472 bool Value::QuickIsUndefined() const {
11473  typedef internal::Address A;
11474  typedef internal::Internals I;
11475  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11476  if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11477  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11478  return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kUndefinedOddballKind);
11479 }

11507 bool Value::QuickIsNullOrUndefined() const {
11508  typedef internal::Address A;
11509  typedef internal::Internals I;
11510  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11511  if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11512  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11513  int kind = I::GetOddballKind(obj);
11514  return kind == I::kNullOddballKind || kind == I::kUndefinedOddballKind;
11515 }

11899  I::IntToSmi(I::kInferShouldThrowMode)) {

11965 
11966 int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
11967  int64_t change_in_bytes) {
11968  typedef internal::Internals I;
11969  int64_t* external_memory = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
11970  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);
11971  int64_t* external_memory_limit = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
11972  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryLimitOffset);
11973  int64_t* external_memory_low_since_mc =
11974  reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
11975  I::kExternalMemoryLowSinceMarkCompactOffset);
11976 
11977  // Embedders are weird: we see both over- and underflows here. Perform the
11978  // addition with unsigned types to avoid undefined behavior.
11979  const int64_t amount =
11980  static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<uint64_t>(change_in_bytes) +
11981  static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory));
11982  *external_memory = amount;
11983 
11984  if (amount < *external_memory_low_since_mc) {
11985  *external_memory_low_since_mc = amount;
11986  *external_memory_limit = amount + I::kExternalAllocationSoftLimit;
11987  }
11988 
11989  if (change_in_bytes <= 0) return *external_memory;
11990 
11991  if (amount > *external_memory_limit) {
11992  ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
11993  }
11994  return *external_memory;
11995 }
11996 
11997 Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
11998 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11999  typedef internal::Address A;
12000  typedef internal::Internals I;
12001  A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
12002  A embedder_data =
12003  I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
12004  int value_offset =
12005  I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
12006  A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(embedder_data, value_offset);
12007 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
12008  // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
12009  // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
12010  value =
12011  I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(embedder_data, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
12012 #endif
12013  internal::Isolate* isolate = internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(
12014  *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this));
12015  A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
12016  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
12017 #else
12018  return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
12019 #endif
12020 }
12021 
12022 
12023 void* Context::GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(int index) {
12024 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
12025  typedef internal::Address A;
12026  typedef internal::Internals I;
12027  A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
12028  A embedder_data =
12029  I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
12030  int value_offset =
12031  I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
12032  internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(ctx);
12033  return reinterpret_cast<void*>(
12034  I::ReadExternalPointerField(isolate, embedder_data, value_offset));
12035 #else
12036  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(index);
12037 #endif
12038 }
